alertbanner.dismiss.comment: AlertBanner component can have a dissmiss button to close it. This string is displayed in a tooltip when hovering over the dismiss button.

alertinline.dismiss.comment: AlertInline component can have a dissmiss button to close it. This string is displayed in a tooltip when hovering over the dismiss button.

alertmodal.label.details.comment: Label for a button in the AlertModal component which trigger the display of more information for the user.

avatar.label.alt.comment: Is read by screen reader. This is used as alt property of the Avatar image.

dialog.actions.close.comment: Appear at the bottom of some dialog/modals in the bottom right. This is a default actions provided to the user to close the dialog/modal.

dialog.header.back.comment: Appear in an icon button of dialog/modal in the upper left corner to go back to the previous step.

dialog.header.close.comment: Appear in a tooltip of dialog/modal in the upper right corner to close it

fieldlabel.optional.comment: Appear after the label of a field inside parentheses to indicate that the field is optional.

inline-edit.cancel.comment: Text for screen reader in the inline edit component to cancel the change that has been done and closing the edition mode.

inline-edit.save.comment: Text for screen reader in the inline edit component to save the change that has been done and closing the edition mode.

input.clear.comment: Appear in input field when the clear action is available. It is displayed in a tooltip when hovering over the clear button.

menu.secondaryaction.label.comment: Label for an icon button used as a secondary action in a menu item to open the link in a new browser tab.

progress.circular.loading.comment: Is read by screen reader. This is used as aria-label property of the visual circular progress to indicate this is a loading state.

panel.action.resize.comment: Appear in a tooltip of panel in the upper right corner to resize it

select.comboboxeditable.clear.comment: Appear in MultiSelect when there is more than one option selected. This action removes all selected tags. It is displayed in a tooltip when hovering over the clear button.

select.createoption.label.comment: Appear at the end of every option that match the filter to propose to the user to create a new option in the list. The string is concatenated to the typed value by the user to create the corresponding sentence: Create ${typedinput}

select.dropdown.search.placeholder.comment: Placeholder text in the search input field that is displayed in Select dropdown component.

select.dropdown.no-results.message.comment: Message displayed when no option match the current filter in Select dropdown component.

table.column.visilibty-form.search.aria-.comment: Label used by screen readers in the Table component under the column manage actions.

table.column.visilibty-form.search.place.comment: Placeholder text in the search input field in the Table component under the column manage actions.

table.column.visibility-form.selectall.l.comment: Label displayed in visibility-form to let the user express he wants to see all columns.

table.header.select-all.aria-label.comment: Aria Label used by screen reader on top of a checkbox input to let the user select all the rows inside the table.

table.header.select-radio.aria-label.comment: Aria Label used by screen reader on top of a radio input to let the user select a current column.

table.header.select-multiple.aria-label.comment: Aria Label used by screen reader on top of a checkbox input to let the user select multiple columns.

table.header.sort-ascending.label.comment: Label displayed in a dropdown menu available in the header of each column to let the user sort the column in ascending order.

table.header.sort-descending.label.comment: Label displayed in a dropdown menu available in the header of each column to let the user sort the column in descending order.

table.header.hide-column.label.comment: Label displayed in a dropdown menu available in the header of each column to let the user hide the column.

table.header.manage-columns-visbility.la.comment: Label displayed in a dropdown menu available in the header of each column to let the user manage the visibility of the columns.

table.header.more-actions.aria-label.comment: Aria Label used by screen reader on top of a button to let the user access more actions.

table.header.resize-column.aria-label.comment: Aria Label used by screen reader on top of a button to let the user resize the column.

table.cell.menu.aria-label.comment: Aria Label used by screen reader on top of a button to let the user access more actions contextual to a table cell.

table.norows.message.default-title.comment: This title is displayed at the center of table which have no rows and if the dev didn't change the default message

table.row.selection.aria-label.comment: Aria Label used by screen reader on top of a checkbox input to let the user select a row of the current table.

table.body.loadmore.label.comment: Label for the button to load more rows in the table when the user use a touch only device.

tag.remove.comment: Appear in Tag component if they can be removed. The action remove the corresponding Tag. It is displayed in a tooltip when hovering over the remove button.

toast.dismiss.comment: Toast component have a dissmiss button to close it. This string is displayed in a tooltip when hovering over the dismiss button.

treeitem.label.close.comment: Aria label for the button to collapse a tree item in the Tree component.

treeitem.label.expand.comment: Aria label for the button to expand a tree item in the Tree component.
